Devices (2)<br>
Restraining Bolt x2<br>
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is a frustrating deck for most LS ground decks.  The Undercover Droids effectively block force drains, while at the same time allowing me to flip my objective.  The Restraining Bolted Probe Droid makes my opponent's drains -1 on the planet where I deploy him, without giving me the headache of worrying about him being battled.<br>
<br>
Probe droids also soak up a ton of damage because of their forfeits.  So Vader, Tarkin and 2 or three Probe Droids can hold out in a battle for quite awhile.<br>
<br>
Against Hidden Base I can deploy Star Destroyers quickly because of the amount of force generation provided by my opponent.  I use Probe Droids to probe and this causes double damage along with Security Precautions since I retrieve 1 force for every probe card that was a droid, even while my opponent is losing force for Precautions.<br>
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech SW: CCG <BR> Play With Power <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
